  "prompt": "What is the difference between training & development?",
  "response": "Training and development are related but distinct concepts in human resource management:\n\nTraining:\n1. Short-term focus\n2. Specific skill-based learning\n3. Immediate job performance improvement\n4. Targeted at current job requirements\n5. Often structured and formal\n6. Standardized content\n7. Measurable immediate outcomes\n8. Typically task-oriented\n9. Addresses current skill gaps\n10. Usually job-specific\n\nDevelopment:\n1. Long-term perspective\n2. Broader professional growth\n3. Career progression and potential\n4. Focuses on future capabilities\n5. More flexible and personalized\n6. Individualized learning paths\n7. Emphasizes overall personal growth\n8. Strategic and holistic approach\n9. Prepares employees for future roles\n10. Includes leadership and soft skills\n\nKey Differences:\n- Scope: Training is narrow, development is broad\n- Timeframe: Training is short-term, development is long-term\n- Purpose: Training improves current performance, development prepares for future opportunities\n- Orientation: Training is job-specific, development is career-oriented\n\nWhile different, training and development are complementary and both essential for organizational and individual growth.",
